</div></div></section></section><section id="s014"><h2 class="pmc_sec_title">Acknowledgments</h2>
<p>This study was supported by a grant from the McKesson Foundation, Mobilizing for Health Grant Program, and by a National Library of Medicine training grant, Biomedical Informatics Research Training at Oregon Health and Science University, T15LM007088, and the National Center for Advancing Translational Sciences of the National Institutes of Health under award number UL1TR000128. These sponsoring organizations had no role in the design and conduct of the study. The content is solely the responsibility of the authors and does not necessarily represent the official views of the National Institutes of Health.</p>
<p>The authors thank David Choi, MD MS, for his innovative graphics; James Case, MS, for his careful design of Mammopad; and Kathryn I. Pyle, AMLS, MA, for her editing expertise. The authors also thank the clinicians and staff of the participating clinics: Aumsville Medical Clinic, Stayton Family Practice, and Santiam Medical Associates. Written permission has been obtained from all people listed in the acknowledgments.</p></section><section id="s015"><h2 class="pmc_sec_title">Author Disclosure Statement</h2>
<p>No competing financial interests exist.</p></section><section id="ref-list1" class="ref-list"><h2 class="pmc_sec_title">References</h2>
